title: theBalm - Meet Matt(e) Nude Eyeshadow Palette
summary: Creamy, dreamy... a must for 40+ women
reviewText:
I received these yesterday and had to apply very quickly. If you are 40 or older you should switch to matte eye shadows. For years I thought I just wasn't photogenic. Then I read a few articles, switched to matte and couldn't believe the difference. I start with Loreal magic de-crease eyelid primer. I have tried other more expensive brands (like Urban Decay), but they aren't created for more mature eyes. Another help to me was finding celebrities with eyes shaped like mine, and look at their make-up application. For me it was Olivia Wilde. I also found a chart in pintrest showing one eye shape with multiple applications of eyeliner that changed the way I apply that as well.

Back to this product. It's creamy versus chalky. Any matte you find in grocery stores will be chalky. I have been using Stila. But this is better.  And it just takes a small amount. The colors are great as well. One of my favorite make-up products ever.

title: theBalm Bahama Mama Bronzer w/ Mini Mary-Lou Manizer
reviewText:
I considered a lot of options for a drugstore priced bronzer: Physician's Formula, NYX, NYC, the Body Shop. I had a bad experience with a Physician's Formula bronzer which had good shades but a lot of sparkles. This bronzer, on the other hand, is a good matte bronzer. The shade looked a little too dark on the pan, but it was subtle on my face once I applied it with a contour brush. I have asian skin so it's easy for a lot of bronzers to look too orange or muddy on my skin. This one was good after one application. I found that if I applied too much, it made me look like I had dirt on my face. I'm not sure if this is the perfect shade for contouring, but I'm satisfied with the results. I can apply this, and still have natural looking makeup.
 I tried the Twinbeauty Prop Bronzer Brush, but it wasn't that great. I think I would be better off just buying the bronzer without the brush. The bristles were not dense enough, and they fell out after one wash. It's useful for a very light application of the bronzer, but it is not suited for my daily makeup routine. I found the contour brush from Real Techniques was a good match for the bronzer. The brush is the reason why I detracted a star off the rating.
I would recommend it to people who have ivory or beige toned skin. If you are really fair or dark skin, it might not be a good shade for you.
combined: Summary: Five Stars; Content: Everything went fine, cheers

title: theBalm Cucumber Face Toner, 6 fl. oz.
reviewText:
I have used cucumber toners in the past, one of my favorites being one by Aubrey Organics which regrettably was recently discontinued. While looking for an alternative, I came across this TimeBalm Toner and ordered it.

I should have known from the start that this would likely be a disappointing experience because this product had no cucumber scent at all. Where my Aubrey toner had a wonderful cucumber smell, this one smelled more chemical than anything else.

But I wanted to be fair and try it out before judging. However, whatever is in this stuff makes my skin burn and dries it out a lot. I could not put face oil and moisturizer on fast enough after using this product. The burning sensation also lingered long after the moisturizer/oil were absorbed. Additionally I developed temporary red, angry patches every time - it looked as if I exfoliated my face for too long.

I can't recall that I ever had such a reaction to a toner and will probably toss it or give it away. It is obviously not made for sensitive skin like mine.
combined: Summary: Great deal!; Content: Great deal

reviewText: Perfect for my purse. And the pigmentations is strong and beautiful
combined: Summary: Hands down my favorite powder I've ever tried!!!!; Content: This powder gives the most lightweight anf full coverage I have ever used my entire life apart from airbrushed at the salon. It's way better than mineral makeup and has never left my face oily at the end of a long day.  I don't even have to reapply the entire time at work, it covers as great by the end of the day as it does at the beg.  I use it with Urban Decay concealer and I love it, zero need for foundation.  I don't even need a concealer unless I've had a breakout around that time of the month, it's that great. I have some acne scars and redness on my skin and you'd never be able to guess I was even wearing makeup or I had any blemish or skin problems. I have an oily Tzone and by the end of the day using L'Oral I'd have to use oil blotting pads because the oil was just so thick and overwhelming I couldn't take it.  I've never had this problem using Stilla and better yet, I don't even have to use 1/2 the makeup products Id normally wear to achieve this level of amazing.  So, yes the price is a Lil steep ( in the grand scheme of makeup prices-not really, versus drugstore or Walmart makeup brands it's def more expensive.) But if you take in account the fact you'll never need foundation and one compact lasts me a little over a month then it will actually save you money in the long run, plus the confidence and look you will feel from using it. TOTALLY WORTH IT!!! I promise I wasn't paid to say this, and I never write reviews.  I had to though on this one, you'll never even think of another makeup routine after this.

title: theBalm NUDE 'tude Eyeshadow Palette w/ Twinbeauty Classic Eyeshadow Brush
reviewText:
These colors are adorbs and very pigmented. They're great for blending and you don't need a lot to achieve a bright, defined eye look. They were also so kind as to include an eyeshadow brush on top of the dual-purpose one included in the palette, so if you don't like how one works, you can try the other. The mirror is very nice as well; I can pretty much see my entire face on it.

My last thought concerns the design. How cute is it that the palette features pretty pinup girls? I was already sold on the quality of the shadows and colors (several of which aren't usually included in most nude palettes like the pale pink, the sandy color and the reddish brown it features) but its great when a product is just overall nice to look at. Would definitely purchase again.

title: theBalm TimeBalm Concealer
reviewText: I found this little item on the same site as I found the Egyptian Magic talking about how fabulous it was and how all of the stars use it, etc.  Maybe it works for them but for me, it just sort of runs for my wrinkles and screams, "Oh, hey!  Look!  I'm a wrinkle!"  I've tried to use it as a cover up for spot touch ups since it doesn't seem to work as a wrinkle concealer but it's kind of greasy and doesn't really do the trick there either.  I won't buy it again and I'm not sure that I'd recommend it to someone else.
combined: Summary: Still using after 8 years; Content: Fit right in the compact case--which I bought maybe 8 years ago, so was worth the purchase despite what some other reviewers say--and has stayed put. This is the only item of makeup I still use after my complexion has changed from mid-20s to my rosacea-cursed 30s, and I now have different makeup needs and more expensive tastes. It has stood the test of time, even against the more "elite" makeup brands. Great for sensitive skin, stays on my face, blends right in, doesn't get messed up if I have a bit of sweat at the time.

title: theBalm TimeBalm Face Primer, 1 fl. oz./30mL
reviewText: TheBalm products have not disaapointed me. This primer does what it says and helps my foundation go on smoothly and stay on! I have normal skin and my sister with real oily skin did mention that she had to use a bit of powder to help with shine by mid-day. I have even worn this alone and it does help to reduce pore size (I have large pores) and give a smooth appearance. I have tried other products and this primer is by far the best. A little goes a long way, so this generous tube is well worth it for the price!

Summary: Very nice!; Content: On days when I want to just brush and go, this is my go-to product.  The coverage is all that I need, if I want more, I simply wet my brush.  It blends wonderfully, has a nice matte finish, and I'll always have it in my makeup arsenal.
